<div class="p-6 mx-auto max-w-3xl sm:pt-12 sm:pb-16 lg:pt-16">
  <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-center sm:text-7xl text-balance text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100">
    Record every shot.<br>
    Learn what works.<br>
    Drink better coffee.
  </h1>
  <p class="mt-12 text-xl leading-8 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
    I built Visualizer to keep all my coffee data in one place instead of scattered across files, apps, and half-remembered notes.
    Store your shots, compare curves, keep the details that matter, and use it all to drink and enjoy better coffee.
  </p>
  <div class="flex gap-x-12 justify-center items-center mt-12">
    <% path = authenticated? ? shots_path : new_registration_path %>
    <%= link_to "Get started", path, class: "button-terracotta px-3.5 py-2.5" %>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="py-6 px-6 mx-auto max-w-5xl lg:px-8">
  <iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/7JPgoQLHvss" title="Video" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen class="w-full aspect-video"></iframe>
</div>
<div class="py-12 sm:py-16">
  <div class="px-6 mx-auto max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:text-center">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-balance text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-500">Made by a coffee nerd, for coffee nerds</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 font-serif text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">Less guesswork, better coffee</p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
        Whether you're a home enthusiast or a professional barista, Visualizer gives you the tools to understand your coffee better.
        Track your progress, experiment with confidence, and keep all your coffee data in one place.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mx-auto mt-16 max-w-2xl sm:mt-20 lg:mt-24 lg:max-w-4xl">
      <dl class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-10 max-w-xl lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-y-16 lg:max-w-none">
        <div class="relative pl-16">
          <dt class="text-xl font-bold leading-7 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <div class="flex absolute top-0 left-0 justify-center items-center rounded-lg size-10 bg-terracotta-600">
              <svg class="text-white size-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 16.5V9.75m0 0l3 3m-3-3l-3 3M6.75 19.5a4.5 4.5 0 01-1.41-8.775 5.25 5.25 0 0110.233-2.33 3 3 0 013.758 3.848A3.752 3.752 0 0118 19.5H6.75z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            Works with your setup
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
            Visualizer started with
            <a href="https://decentespresso.com/" class="standard-link" target="_blank">Decent espresso machines</a>,
            <a href="https://beanconqueror.com/" class="standard-link" target="_blank">Beanconqueror</a>,
            <a href="https://gaggiuino.github.io/" class="standard-link" target="_blank">Gaggiuino</a>,
            <a href="https://gaggimate.eu/" class="standard-link" target="_blank">GaggiMate</a>,
            <a href="https://www.meticuloushome.com/" class="standard-link" target="_blank">Meticulous</a>,
            <a href="https://www.naked-portafilter.com/product-category/smart-espresso-profiler/" class="standard-link" target="_blank">Smart Espresso Profiler</a>,
            <a href="https://pressensor.com/" class="standard-link" target="_blank">Pressensor</a>,
            and more. If your workflow produces useful coffee data, there is a good chance Visualizer can do something nice with it.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="relative pl-16">
          <dt class="text-xl font-bold leading-7 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <div class="flex absolute top-0 left-0 justify-center items-center rounded-lg size-10 bg-terracotta-600">
              <svg class="text-white size-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3.75 3v11.25A2.25 2.25 0 006 16.5h2.25M3.75 3h-1.5m1.5 0h16.5m0 0h1.5m-1.5 0v11.25A2.25 2.25 0 0118 16.5h-2.25m-7.5 0h7.5m-7.5 0l-1 3m8.5-3l1 3m0 0l.5 1.5m-.5-1.5h-9.5m0 0l-.5 1.5m.75-9l3-3 2.148 2.148A12.061 12.061 0 0116.5 7.605" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            Compare what changed
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
            Upload a shot and you get charts, metadata, notes, coffee context, and side-by-side comparison in one place.
            That makes it much easier to answer the useful questions: what changed, what helped, and which shot is worth repeating.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="relative pl-16">
          <dt class="text-xl font-bold leading-7 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <div class="flex absolute top-0 left-0 justify-center items-center rounded-lg size-10 bg-terracotta-600">
              <svg class="text-white size-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M18 18.72a9.094 9.094 0 003.741-.479 3 3 0 00-4.682-2.72m.94 3.198l.001.031c0 .225-.012.447-.037.666A11.944 11.944 0 0112 21c-2.17 0-4.207-.576-5.963-1.584A6.062 6.062 0 016 18.719m12 0a5.971 5.971 0 00-.941-3.197m0 0A5.995 5.995 0 0012 12.75a5.995 5.995 0 00-5.058 2.772m0 0a3 3 0 00-4.681 2.72 8.986 8.986 0 003.74.477m.94-3.197a5.971 5.971 0 00-.94 3.197M15 6.75a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2.25 2.25 0 11-4.5 0 2.25 2.25 0 014.5 0zm-13.5 0a2.25 2.25 0 11-4.5 0 2.25 2.25 0 014.5 0z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            Learn from other shots
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
            Over <%= number_with_delimiter(@user_count) %> coffee people use Visualizer to share shots, compare results, and swap profiles.
            Sometimes you want to geek out over your own data, and sometimes you just want to see what somebody else did to make a coffee sing.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="relative pl-16">
          <dt class="text-xl font-bold leading-7 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <div class="flex absolute top-0 left-0 justify-center items-center rounded-lg size-10 bg-terracotta-600">
              <svg class="text-white size-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M14.25 7.756a4.5 4.5 0 100 8.488M7.5 10.5h5.25m-5.25 3h5.25M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            Premium if you want even more
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
            The Visualizer free forever tier includes uploads, charts, comparison, sharing, and everyday shot analysis.
            Premium adds full history, coffee management, tags, private notes, custom fields, Airtable sync, and more for €5/month or €50/year, with <%= free_trial_days %>-day free trial.
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="py-12 sm:py-16">
  <div class="px-6 mx-auto max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid overflow-hidden grid-cols-1 gap-8 mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:grid-cols-4 lg:mx-0 lg:max-w-none">
      <div>
        <time datetime="2020-11" class="flex items-center font-serif text-lg font-semibold leading-6 text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-500">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 4 4" class="flex-none mr-4 size-1">
            <circle cx="2" cy="2" r="2" fill="currentColor" />
          </svg>
          Nov 2020
          <div class="absolute -ml-2 w-screen h-px -translate-x-full sm:-ml-4 lg:static lg:flex-auto lg:ml-8 lg:-mr-6 lg:w-auto lg:translate-x-0 bg-neutral-900/10 dark:bg-neutral-100/10"></div>
        </time>
        <p class="mt-6 font-serif text-2xl font-bold lining-nums tracking-tight leading-8 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <a href="https://public.3.basecamp.com/p/3bpv4ybEVekQVXy7Ud9vW6n1" class="standard-link" target="_blank">
            First commit
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-7 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
          Just hours after unboxing a Decent espresso machine in November 2020, the first iteration of Visualizer was created and shared with the community.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <time datetime="2022-01" class="flex items-center font-serif text-lg font-semibold leading-6 text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-500">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 4 4" class="flex-none mr-4 size-1">
            <circle cx="2" cy="2" r="2" fill="currentColor" />
          </svg>
          Jan 2022
          <div class="absolute -ml-2 w-screen h-px -translate-x-full sm:-ml-4 lg:static lg:flex-auto lg:ml-8 lg:-mr-6 lg:w-auto lg:translate-x-0 bg-neutral-900/10 dark:bg-neutral-100/10"></div>
        </time>
        <p class="mt-6 font-serif text-2xl font-bold lining-nums tracking-tight leading-8 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <a href="/updates/visualizer-v3" class="standard-link" target="_blank">
            Switching to SaaS
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-7 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
          In 2022, I switched from a sponsorship model to a freemium subscription model.
          The goal was to cover hosting costs, keep the free tier useful, and make it possible to keep building new features at a sensible pace.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <time datetime="2023-12" class="flex items-center font-serif text-lg font-semibold leading-6 text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-500">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 4 4" class="flex-none mr-4 size-1">
            <circle cx="2" cy="2" r="2" fill="currentColor" />
          </svg>
          Dec 2023
          <div class="absolute -ml-2 w-screen h-px -translate-x-full sm:-ml-4 lg:static lg:flex-auto lg:ml-8 lg:-mr-6 lg:w-auto lg:translate-x-0 bg-neutral-900/10 dark:bg-neutral-100/10"></div>
        </time>
        <p class="mt-6 font-serif text-2xl font-bold lining-nums tracking-tight leading-8 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <a href="/updates/visualizer-v4" class="standard-link" target="_blank">
            Visualizer gets a logo
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-7 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
          In December 2023, I made a complete redesign with a proper logo, a cleaner interface, and faster ways to browse through shots.
          It was the point where the project started to feel less like a handy tool and more like a real home for all coffee data.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <time datetime="2025-12" class="flex items-center font-serif text-lg font-semibold leading-6 text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-500">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 4 4" class="flex-none mr-4 size-1">
            <circle cx="2" cy="2" r="2" fill="currentColor" />
          </svg>
          Dec 2025
          <div class="absolute -ml-2 w-screen h-px -translate-x-full sm:-ml-4 lg:static lg:flex-auto lg:ml-8 lg:-mr-6 lg:w-auto lg:translate-x-0 bg-neutral-900/10 dark:bg-neutral-100/10"></div>
        </time>
        <p class="mt-6 font-serif text-2xl font-bold lining-nums tracking-tight leading-8 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <a href="/updates/thank-you-for-the-first-5-years" class="standard-link" target="_blank">
            The First 5 Years
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-7 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
          Five years after that first release, Visualizer had grown from a small Decent side project into a home for millions of shots and a much broader coffee community.
          A look back on how it started, what changed along the way, and why I am still excited to keep building it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<% if @last_update.present? %>
  <div class="py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="px-6 pb-16 mx-auto max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-6xl text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-300">
          Latest Updates
        </h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-12 px-6 mx-auto max-w-7xl sm:gap-y-16 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:px-8">
      <article class="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl lg:mx-0 lg:max-w-lg">
        <time datetime="<%= @last_update.published_at.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") %>" class="block text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <%= @last_update.published_at.strftime("%b %d, %Y") %>
        </time>
        <h2 id="featured-post" class="mt-4">
          <%= link_to @last_update.title, update_path(@last_update.slug.presence || @last_update.id), class: "font-serif text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 hover:text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-300 dark:hover:text-neutral-400 sm:text-4xl", target: "_blank" %>
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <%= @last_update.excerpt %>
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 justify-between mt-4 sm:flex-row-reverse sm:gap-8 sm:mt-8 lg:flex-col lg:mt-4">
          <div class="flex">
            <%= link_to "Continue reading →", update_path(@last_update.slug.presence || @last_update.id), class: "text-sm font-semibold leading-6 text-terracotta-600 hover:text-terracotta-500 dark:text-terracotta-500 dark:hover:text-terracotta-400", target: "_blank" %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
      <div class="pt-12 mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl border-t sm:pt-16 lg:pt-0 lg:mx-0 lg:max-w-none lg:border-t-0 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700">
        <div class="-my-12 divide-y divide-neutral-200 dark:divide-neutral-700">
          <% @updates.each do |update| %>
            <article class="py-12">
              <div class="relative max-w-xl group">
                <time datetime="<%= update.published_at.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") %>" class="block text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                  <%= update.published_at.strftime("%b %d, %Y") %>
                </time>
                <h2 class="mt-2 font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 text dark:text-neutral-300 group-hover:text-neutral-400">
                  <%= link_to update_path(update.slug.presence || update.id), target: "_blank" do %>
                    <span class="absolute inset-0"></span>
                    <%= update.title %>
                  <% end %>
                </h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                  <%= update.excerpt %>
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
<% end %>
